# Applications — folder structure

Every project under `applications/` uses this layout. Shared rules live only in root `.cursor/rules/`. Do not keep parallel copies under `applications/rules/`, `applications/.cursor/`, or `applications/{project}/.cursor/`.

## Required layout per project

`applications/{project}/`

1. **Project root** — build scripts and project-level config only (e.g. `build_*_docs.py`).
2. **`documents/`** — exactly three synced deliverables:
   - `{project}_pdf.pdf`
   - `{project}_ppt.pptx`
   - `{project}_word.docx`
   No drafts, duplicates, or legacy copies in this folder or elsewhere in the project.
3. **`rules/`** — call-specific source of truth only (`source_of_truth.mdc`). One copy; never mirror the same full file under `.cursor/`.

## Opportunities (outside applications/)

`opportunities/` keeps its tracker, build script, and `rules/source_of_truth.mdc`. Same rule: one SoT copy; no second tree under `opportunities/.cursor/`.

## Shared rules (root)

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `folder_structure.mdc` | This layout |
| `documents.mdc` | Cross-format document sync |
| `awief.mdc` / `fid.mdc` / `opportunities.mdc` | Short pointers with globs → project SoT |

## Assets & temp

- Media may come from repo `assets/` or a project `assets/` subfolder.
- Final edited docs live only in `documents/`.
- Temporary and build artifacts go in repo `tmp/` (gitignored).

## Example

```
.cursor/rules/
  folder_structure.mdc
  documents.mdc
  awief.mdc
  fid.mdc
  opportunities.mdc
applications/
  {project}/
    build_{project}_docs.py
    rules/
      source_of_truth.mdc
    documents/
      {project}_pdf.pdf
      {project}_ppt.pptx
      {project}_word.docx
opportunities/
  build_opportunities.py
  opportunities.xlsx
  rules/
    source_of_truth.mdc
```

No duplicate deliverables and no duplicate full rule trees for the same content.
